# Code changes

- Change only what the task requires. Avoid drive-by refactors, unrelated files, and scope creep.
- Read surrounding code first; align naming, types, imports, and documentation level with the file’s style.
- Prefer reusing and extending existing helpers over parallel implementations. Keep diffs easy to review.
